metadata.name: TWNTIES #34
metadata.description:
TWNTIES is a tribute to the Art Deco movement of the 1920s.

To compose the final image, the project must render the buildings and flying objects in 3D, then generate and overlay the various elements using custom masking functions.

/! \ Rendering may take a bit long on older computers or phones (5-10 seconds) /! \

Press [S] to save a 4000x4000 PNG file of the image (It may take a while. Please wait)

Made with p5.js
3D assets made in Blender

Artist: Estienne
January 2022

metadata.name: Neural Collapse #70
metadata.description:
What happens when your brain overloads, or when you lose control of your giant robot.

A study on the repetition and stacking of a simple but very dynamic structure.

Everything procedurally generated at runtime.
You can find more informations on the piece, its design and origins, here: https://ulucode.com/wp/neural-collapse/

Interactivity : 
- You can hover your mouse on the connectors to close them... temporarily
- Press and hold the mouse button to slightly move the viewpoint.

- Press "a" to increase quality of the antialiasing (3 levels), at the cost of performances. Especially useful on the palettes using outlines.
- Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys 1 to 9 (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). Resolutions ranges from 720 to 7680 pixels. I recommend starting with "4".

GPU recommended. Best performances on Chrome in general.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Sugar & Splice #151
metadata.description:
'Sugar & Splice'

Vibrant somethings, full of flavor, dancing within conjoined boundaries.

Controls:
s: Saves an image of the canvas with the current settings
1-6: Scales the canvas size, from 1 (default, 2048px x 2792px) to 6 (12288px x  16752px)
g: Toggles grain texture
t: Toggles background transparency
f: Toggles fit to screen (layout and other factors will change based on the new size, but overall style, colors, etc will remain the same)
p: Shortcut for large print settings: disables the grain texture and scales the canvas to the largest setting
b: Toggles b-side

metadata.name: Assemble #304
metadata.description:
Assemble is a 2D shape composition with a procedural background texture.

There are two types of shapes, squares and blobs, composed in a grid.

12 color palettes, procedurally generated using a GAN algorithm.

Available in [1:1] and [3:4] resolutions.

--------------------------------------------------

Keys [1-4]

1 - Variation (maintaining resolution)
2 - Variation (changing resolution)
3 - Change color (only in [3:4] resolution)
4 - Save canvas (Live View)

--------------------------------------------------

Made with p5.

-dePaula

metadata.name: Phantoms #128
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

metadata.name: Memo #89
metadata.description:
Memo is a abstract expression of memories written on small pieces of paper, pictures of important moments or a reminder of all the things You have forgotten.

Memo is created with P5JS. Large number of rectangles are packed in loops to the canvas with a random rectangle packing algorithm with simple collision detection. 
The looped area varies from 1 vertical or horizontal rectangle to 8x8 grid. Packed area is created with simple random walking grid loop.
60+ color palettes are handpicked and they can appear reversed. 
One random palette is picked for each piece and p5js.noise() drives the colors, size and angle on the rects with lots of attributes.

Click 'n' to add white noise.
Click 's' to save image as jpeg.

Click '1' to 1x pixelDensity(3600 x 6400 or 6400 x 3600 px - default).
Click '2' to 2x pixelDensity(7200 x 12800 or 12800 x 7200 px).

VGA 2022 / CC BY-NC 4.0

metadata.name: PAMILO GENERATOR® #30
metadata.description:
If you have two names : Bubba and Kiki and two shapes : spike and round. Wich shapes is bubba? and wich shape is Kiki?

This artwork is fully generative, there is not a single png, image, or assets, just P5js and 2 image processing shaders.

Is inspired in the drawings of PAMILO CEIRONE® @nefetesudaca, he has an amazing style completly unique and here is my atemp to try to catch his style using the color palette and the shapes.

Would you dare to find the differents between the capture and the running artwork? Is a magic trick !

Thanks to @cyberhens for introducing me to the amazing artist that is Pamilo, and thanks to the amazing GNFTs community, the largest hiberoamerican generative nft community.
